    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1956-05-23T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1956-05-23T16:00:00-05:00" n="363"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d363">
                <head>363. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Embassy in Egypt</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d363fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 674.84A/5–2356. Secret; Priority. Received at 11:45 p.m.. May 25.
                        Repeated to Amman, Beirut, Baghdad, Damascus, Jidda, Tel Aviv, London, and
                        Paris.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Cairo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1956-05-23T23:00:00+02:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 23, 1956—11 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2318. Saw <persName corresp="#p_HA1">Hussein</persName> briefly right after his
                    initial meeting with <persName corresp="#p_NNNCGA1">Nasser</persName>. <persName
                        corresp="#p_HA1">Hussein</persName> had following points of interest on this
                    first encounter.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>(1)</label>
                    <item>He personally felt completely reassured that <persName
                            corresp="#p_NNNCGA1">Nasser</persName> had no intention of attacking
                        Israel.</item>
                    <label>(2)</label>
                    <item>
                        <persName corresp="#p_NNNCGA1">Nasser</persName>’s feeling on question of
                        arms for Israel was intense. He obviously operating under some type of
                        intelligence unknown to us which indicates that definite decision was made
                        to try to keep Israel as strong as Arab States. He feels blame must be
                        shared but mentioned <persName corresp="#p_ERHSA1">Eden</persName>
                        particularly. He apparently wonders whether things have reached point in
                        Britain where British would even spur Israeli aggressions against Egypt. He
                        felt that real motivation behind rumored arms blockade again lay with
                            <persName corresp="#p_ERHSA1">Eden</persName> and that <persName
                            corresp="#p_ERHSA1">Eden</persName> envisaged type of blockade which
                        Israelis could circumvent as in past hostilities. I told <persName
                            corresp="#p_HA1">Hussein</persName> to pass to <persName
                            corresp="#p_NNNCGA1">Nasser</persName> that I absolutely convinced he
                        operating under false information. Truth was almost entirely to <pb
                            facs="0698" n="670" xml:id="pg_670"/> contrary as <persName
                            corresp="#p_ERHSA1">Eden</persName> had been annoyed at Russian
                        suggestion of arms embargo to Middle East which he saw as move on their part
                        to wreck Baghdad Pact.</item>
                    <label>(3)</label>
                    <item>Secretary should not feel that motive behind recognition Red China was
                        slap at US. Timing of this act had been related solely to establishing new
                        source of arms because of <persName corresp="#p_NNNCGA1">Nasser</persName>’s
                        feelings as above on question arms for Israel. <persName corresp="#p_HA1"
                            >Hussein</persName> said <persName corresp="#p_NNNCGA1"
                            >Nasser</persName> asked that I be told this officially and that he
                        regretted apparent misinterpretation in United States.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BHA1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Byroade</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
